      "span_text": "Surprisingly, [CITATION_1] found that the two hot residues, D898 and D900, with the greatest effect on ⌬ V 0.5 in the electrophysiological assay of Ca 2 ϩ dependence, also have a large inhibitory effect on 45 Ca 2 ϩ binding to the COOH-terminal 240 residues of the mSlo region, 50% and 51%, respectively, as measured for single alanine mutants of these residues (see Fig. 8 A of Bao et al., 2004, in this issue) .",
